<p>The integrity of the SSL system cannot be maintained in secrecy. Incidents like this one demonstrate the need for active, immediate and comprehensive communication between CAs and software vendors to keep our collective users safe online.</p>
<p>Johnathan Nightingale<br>
Director of Firefox Engineering</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/OWASP/~4/A_quJVPgTVQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (author nil "Johnathan Nightingale") (pubDate nil "Fri, 02 Sep 2011 21:28:48 -0400") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://blog.mozilla.com/security/2011/09/02/diginotar-removal-follow-up/"))) ("Most security pros don't think a breach will happen to them" "New findings from a Tenable Network Security study have uncovered an &quot;It Won’t Happen to Me&quot; mentality amongst security professionals.
