<p>These days, creating secure applications is of the utmost importance, and as crackers improve their skills, security is becoming more and more challenging. Developers who are responsible for this area are only as good as the tools available to them. If this is you, and you work on Windows, then you might want to have a look at <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/agnitiotool\">Agnitio</a>. This security review tool assists you in conducting manual security reviews, and provides code review metrics and reporting for static analysis.</p></div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/OWASP/~4/w74K34Hy8Ok\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (author nil "(author unknown)") (pubDate nil "Sun, 21 Aug 2011 20:32:50 -0400") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://sourceforge.net/blog/agnitio/"))) ("Insulin pump attack prompts call for federal probe" "<h4>Security of medical devices questioned</h4> <p>The hack of a commercially available insulin pump that diabetics can control wirelessly has attracted the attention of US lawmakers who oversee the safety of the nation's airwaves.…</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/OWASP/~4/XpZGtrZuQiY\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>" "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/OWASP/~3/XpZGtrZuQiY/" (20046 50754) old 38 nil nil ((title nil "Insulin pump attack prompts call for federal probe") (link nil "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/OWASP/~3/XpZGtrZuQiY/") (description nil "<h4>Security of medical devices questioned</h4> <p>The hack of a commercially available insulin pump that diabetics can control wirelessly has attracted the attention of US lawmakers who oversee the safety of the nation's airwaves.…</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/OWASP/~4/XpZGtrZuQiY\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (author nil "Dan Goodin") (pubDate nil "Fri, 19 Aug 2011 16:23:30 -0400") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://go.theregister.com/feed/www.theregister.co.uk/2011/08/19/insulin_pump_hack/"))) ("AES crypto broken by 'groundbreaking' attack" "<h4>Faster than simp